  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "You are given an array AAA containing NNN integers.\n\nCount the number of **ordered pairs** (i,j)(i, j)(i,j) such that:\n\n\n1\u2264i,j\u2264N1 \\leq i, j \\leq N1\u2264i,j\u2264N, and\nAij\u2264AjA_i^j \\leq A_jAij\u200b\u2264Aj\u200b\n\nThat is, AiA_iAi\u200b raised to the power jjj doesn't exceed AjA_jAj\u200b.\nNote that we're counting ordered pairs, meaning the pair (1,2)(1, 2)(1,2) is different from the pair (2,1)(2, 1)(2,1).\n\n\nInput Format\n\nThe first line of input will contain a single integer TTT, denoting the number of test cases.\nEach test case consists of two lines of input.\n\nThe first line of each test case contains a single integer NNN \u2014 the number of elements in the array.\nThe second line contains NNN space-separated integers A1,A2,\u2026,ANA_1, A_2, \\ldots, A_NA1\u200b,A2\u200b,\u2026,AN\u200b.\n\n\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, output on a new line the number of ordered pairs (i,j)(i, j)(i,j) that satisfy the given condition.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264T\u22641051 \\leq T \\leq 10^51\u2264T\u2264105",
      "1\u2264N\u22642\u22c51051 \\leq N \\leq 2\\cdot 10^51\u2264N\u22642\u22c5105",
      "1\u2264Ai\u22641091 \\leq A_i \\leq 10^91\u2264Ai\u200b\u2264109",
      "The sum of NNN over all test cases won't exceed 2\u22c51052\\cdot 10^52\u22c5105."
    ],
    "inputFormat": "",
    "outputFormat": "",
    "sampleTestCases": [
      {
        "id": "sample_1",
        "input": "3\n3\n2 3 4\n4\n2 7 2 3\n5\n1000 100 1 10 1",
        "output": "1\n4\n14",
        "explanation": "Explanation:\nTest case 111: The only valid pair is (1,1)(1, 1)(1,1), since Aij=21\u22642=AjA_i^j = 2^1 \\leq 2 = A_jAij\u200b=21\u22642=Aj\u200b.\n(1,3)(1, 3)(1,3) is an invalid pair for example, since Aij=23=8>4=AjA_i^j = 2^3 = 8 \\gt 4 = A_jAij\u200b=23=8>4=Aj\u200b. The same can be verified for all the other pairs.\nTest case 222: The valid pairs are (1,1),(1,2),(3,1),(3,2)(1, 1), (1, 2), (3, 1), (3, 2)(1,1),(1,2),(3,1),(3,2).\nTest case 333: The valid pairs are:\n(1,1),(1, 1),(1,1),\n(2,1),(2, 1),(2,1),\n(3,1),(3,2),(3,3),(3,4),(3,5),(3, 1), (3, 2), (3, 3), (3, 4), (3, 5),(3,1),(3,2),(3,3),(3,4),(3,5),\n(4,1),(4,2),(4, 1), (4, 2),(4,1),(4,2),\n(5,1),(5,2),(5,3),(5,4),(5,5).(5, 1), (5, 2), (5, 3), (5, 4), (5, 5).(5,1),(5,2),(5,3),(5,4),(5,5)."
      }
    ]
